commentary: Utseya to Younis Khan, 1 run, OUT Has Younis run himself out? Yes he has . This is hit wide of deep midwicket, and Younis stutters before starting for the second. Waller's throw is flat and quick, and even a dive from Younis is not good enough. They didn't run the first one fast, and were never too keen on the second until -without a hint of disagreement - they both decided to go for the second. Younis had just survived a plumb lbw call in the last over

commentary: Chigumbura to Shoaib Malik, OUT Taibu has pulled off a blinder, and another comeback man has failed! This will rad as a wicket for the bowler, but it is all down to Taibu. He saw this ball sliding down leg, and moved exceptionally early in anticipation. Malik got a thick edge down the leg side, and Taibu flew across to his left to pouch this one-handed. Smart and athletic both at the same time

commentary: Mpofu to Umar Akmal, OUT a wicket first ball for Mpofu Khan! He digs this in short, not much venom behind it, and Umar goes for the pull, only managing to hit it as far as midwicket's throat. Not the greatest wicket Mpofu has got, but a big one in the context of this game. Powerplay will be taken next over, and they have sent back the dangerous Umar

commentary: Sohail Tanvir to Chibhabha, OUT Too good. Simply too good. Can't do too much about these deliveries. Would have got some of the greats of the game out. He goes wide of the crease, pitches this short of a length, on middle and off, Chibhabha plays the angle, and then the off-cut comes into the play. It moves away slightly, hits the top of off. Just doff your hat, and walk off, Justice

commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Masakadza, OUT Hafeez! Hafeez looks innocuous when compared to Ajmal, but he is also getting them wickets! Masakadza moves too far across and tries to play this offbreak square as opposed to down the ground. Misses, and is hit in front of middle. commentary: Aizaz Cheema to Sibanda, OUT What a way to go! Sibanda is caught-and-bowled and bat-pad! To the insult he has added an injury! He gives this length ball some humpty, and the thick inside edge hits his back pad, and it lobs off to Cheema who delightfully completes a simple catch. Sibanda is on the ground, that ball might have hit his knee. He has to be helped off the pitch. The medical support carry his gloves and pads for him as he hobbles off

commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Taibu, no run History 101, where are you? Near run-out. Pushed to cover. Taylor wants one. Taibu doesn't. Sent back. Taylor has to dive. Hafeez seems to have disturbed the stumps without collecting the ball for the second time today. The replays are not conclusive, but it's possible the ball might have hit the stump before Hafeez's hand did so. Benefit of doubt to the batsman, who was definitely out of the crease when the bails came off

commentary: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, no run low full toss, Chigumbura goes across its line, looking for the biog slog, doesn't connect at all. Advantage Pakistan
shortText: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, no run
text: low full toss, Chigumbura goes across its line, looking for the biog slog, doesn't connect at all. Advantage Pakistan

commentary: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, 1 run another low full toss, Elton can't get under it, gets just the single to cover. Applause from Pakistan's support staff
shortText: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, 1 run

commentary: Junaid Khan to Lamb, 1 run another full toss, Lamb hits it square, but finds point, Six feet either side, and he would have got four
shortText: Junaid Khan to Lamb, 1 run
text: another full toss, Lamb hits it square, but finds point, Six feet either side, and he would have got four

commentary: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, 1 run, OUT another low full toss, and Chigumbura goes down the ground. The mis-hit lands short of long-off, Umar Akmal fumbles there, but makes up for it with a flat throw at the striker's end to get Chigumbura out
shortText: Junaid Khan to Chigumbura, 1 run, OUT
text: another low full toss, and Chigumbura goes down the ground. The mis-hit lands short of long-off, Umar Akmal fumbles there, but makes up for it with a flat throw at the striker's end to get Chigumbura out

commentary: Junaid Khan to Utseya, 1 run He has taken guard at sixth stump outside off, he is going to slog it to leg. Gets the length ball too, but can't time it well enough to clear the midwicket boundary. Heartbreak for Zimbabwe, bullet bitten by Pakistan
